addPrediction(uint256,uint256).details: Uses LMSR pricing - popular entries cost more

params.amount: Amount of payment token to deposit

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

params.entryId: The entry to get price for

cancelContest().details: Cannot cancel after settlement - settlement is final

params.entryId: The entry to claim payout for

closePredictions().details: Prevents last-second predictions when outcome is nearly certain  Use case: Close predictions when final round starts, before results are known This prevents unfair late predictions and potential race conditions

params._contestantDepositAmount: Fixed amount each contestant must deposit
params._paymentToken: ERC20 token used for deposits and payouts
params._prizeShareBps: Portion of spectator deposit going to prize pool (e.g., 750 = 7.5%)
params._userShareBps: Portion of spectator deposit going to contestant bonuses (e.g., 750 = 7.5%)

distributeExpiredContest().details: Can only be called after expiryTimestamp has passed  This function distributes all unclaimed winnings to their rightful owners: - Pushes unclaimed entry payouts - Pushes unclaimed spectator payouts (winners only)  Use case: Users forgot to claim or lost access to accounts. After expiry, oracle can force distribution to prevent funds being locked forever.

joinContest(uint256).details: Must deposit exact contestantDepositAmount per entry

leaveContest(uint256).details: Works in OPEN state (before contest starts) or CANCELLED state (full refund)Automatically refunds all spectators who predicted on this entry

settleContest(uint256[],uint256[]).details: ONE call does everything!First entry in winningEntries is the overall winner (for spectator market)Entries not included are assumed to have 0% payout

params.payoutBps: Array of payout basis points (must sum to 10000)
params.winningEntries: Array of winning entry IDs (only entries with payouts > 0)

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the ERC]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.

withdrawPrediction(uint256,uint256).details: Works in: - OPEN state (during registration, before competition starts) - CANCELLED state (full refund anytime) NOT allowed in ACTIVE state - once competition starts, predictions are locked

activateContest().notice: Oracle activates the contest (closes entry registration, predictions continue)

addPrediction(uint256,uint256).notice: Spectator adds a prediction by predicting on a specific entry

calculateEntryPrice(uint256).notice: Calculate current LMSR price for an entry

cancelExpired().notice: Anyone can cancel if expired and not settled

claimAllEntryPayouts().notice: User claims payouts for all their entries at once

claimEntryPayout(uint256).notice: User claims payout for a specific entry after settlement

closePredictions().notice: Oracle closes predictions before contest ends

contestPrizePool().notice: Contest prize pool - sum of all contestant entry deposits

contestPrizePoolSubsidy().notice: Contest prize pool subsidy from spectators (7.5% of spectator deposits)

contestantSubsidy(uint256).notice: Contestant subsidies per entry from prediction volume (7.5% of spectator deposits)

demandSensitivityBps().notice: Demand sensitivity in basis points - controls LMSR price curve steepness

distributeExpiredContest().notice: Distribute all unclaimed winnings after contest expires

entries(uint256).notice: Array of entry IDs (for iteration only)

entryOwner(uint256).notice: Maps entry ID to owner address

entryWithdrawn(uint256).notice: Tracks if entry has been withdrawn

finalEntryPayouts(uint256).notice: Final payouts for each entry after settlement

isSpectator(address).notice: Mapping to check if address is a spectator

joinContest(uint256).notice: User joins the contest with a specific entry ID

leaveContest(uint256).notice: User withdraws an entry and gets deposit back

liquidityParameter().notice: LMSR liquidity parameter - controls price curve steepness

netPosition(uint256).notice: Track net position for each entry ID (for LMSR pricing and total supply)

oracle().notice: Address of the oracle that controls contest state

paymentToken().notice: The payment token used for deposits and payouts

predictionPrizePool().notice: Prediction prize pool - collateral backing spectator prediction tokens (~85% of deposits)

prizeShareBps().notice: Portion of spectator deposit that goes to prize pool in basis points (e.g., 750 = 7.5%)

settleContest(uint256[],uint256[]).notice: Oracle settles contest - distributes Layer 1 prizes and resolves Layer 2 market

spectatorDepositedPerEntry(address,uint2.notice: Track deposits per spectator per entry (for auto-refunds on withdrawal)

spectatorMarketResolved().notice: Flag indicating if spectator market has been resolved

spectatorTotalDeposited(address).notice: Track total payment tokens deposited by each spectator (for withdrawals)

spectatorWinningEntry().notice: Winning entry ID after settlement (for winner-take-all)

spectators(uint256).notice: Array of spectator addresses (for forceClose iteration)

userEntries(address,uint256).notice: Track all entry IDs owned by a user

userShareBps().notice: Portion of spectator deposit that goes to contestant bonuses in basis points (e.g., 750 = 7.5%)

withdrawPrediction(uint256,uint256).notice: Spectator withdraws their prediction (burns tokens, gets 100% refund)
